  "body": "Recently I was experimenting with changing `KUBE_EDITOR` for a Golang pre-purposed faux editor when editing resources when I noticed that it couldn't be marshaled. Upon inspecting the output JSON I noticed it had the same comments that the default yaml version has. Valid JSON cannot have comments.\n\nSince the comment also gives warning / error information upon saving it must be decided where to put that in the JSON output. Perhaps a new JSON property?\n## Kubernetes Version:\n\n```\nkubectl version\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"2\", GitVersion:\"v1.2.0\", GitCommit:\"5cb86ee022267586db386f62781338b0483733b3\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\nServer Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"2\", GitVersion:\"v1.2.5\", GitCommit:\"25eb53b54e08877d3789455964b3e97bdd3f3bce\", GitTreeState:\"clean\"}\n```\n## Steps to Reproduce:\n\n```\nkubectl run minio --image=minio/minio --port=9000\nkubectl edit deployment minio -o json\n```\n\n```\n# Please edit the object below. Lines beginning with a '#' will be ignored,\n# and an empty file will abort the edit. If an error occurs while saving this file will be\n# reopened with the relevant failures.\n#\n{\n    \"kind\": \"Deployment\",\n    \"apiVersion\": \"extensions/v1beta1\",\n    \"metadata\": {\n```\n",
